22,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1715022,For Sale:  Heckler & Koch USP .40 S&W Compact,"Indiana, Indiana, United States",$ 740,"Listed On: Tuesday, June 4, 2013",Handguns,Heckler & Koch                                                                                ,40 S&W                                                                                ,no type,Pistol,"Brand new in box, buy it now!! (NO MANUAL SAFETY/DECOCKING LEVER) The HK USP Compact is a small frame pistol capable of firing full power loads. Based on the full-size USP models, these handy pistols combine compact size with optimum effective shooting performance. USP Compacts are smaller and lighter than large frame USPs. The reduction in trigger reach and grip circumference increases concealability and enhances shooting ergonomics. Unlike some subcompact semiautomatic pistols that use a difficult to shoot ""two-finger grip"" frame, the USP Compact uses a narrow, full-hand grip frame with a choice of interchangeable extended or flush-fitting magazine floorplates. This makes the pistol easy to shoot without sacrificing concealability. Like their large frame predecessors, USP Compacts are designed with the demanding needs of the law enforcement and military shooters in mind. Using a modified linkless Browning-type action, the USP Compact is built to take the punishment of high-energy +P loads. To reduce the length of the slide and barrel on the USP Compact, the mechanical recoil reduction system found on large frame USPs has been replaced by a specially designed flat compression spring contained in the captive recoil spring assembly by a polymer absorber bushing. Service life is still engineered to exceed 20,000 rounds. Easy to shoot, simple to maintain; the USP Compact is a reliable, safe, accurate, and highly concealable pistol. Shipping to lower 48 only, Shipping $30.00 KNOW YOUR LOCAL AND STATE LAWS!!
NO TRADE"

Lee should really let you know that a kit such as this one is really only good for reloading jacketed and perhaps plated bullets. 872,http://www.armslist.com/posts/1715872,For Sale/Trade:  All of this pissing and moaning about prices... If you don't like it don't pay it and move on,"Lakeland, Tampa/St. Pete, Florida",$ 1,"Listed On: Tuesday, June 4, 2013",Handguns,Taurus                                                                                ,45 ACP                                                                                ,Double / Single Action                                                                                ,Pistol,"First of all, let me say that I will be just as happy as anyone when the whole firearms market settles down and we see prices start to go back to normal.  I am all for it.
However, in the mean time, I am also all for getting a profit wherever you can, and as the current market stands, it is a sellers market.

What I am not for, is all of these pissing and moaning (and largely uneducated) people  complaining about the prices that people are asking for their weapons and ammunition, ESPECIALLY these morons that rant on here claiming that it is somehow unpatriotic to ""take advantage"" of people during these turbulent times in the market by charging the prices they are.  Every single person who has said this is either uneducated, or understands how the market is supposed to work and just wants to bitch.  Either way these idiots need a lesson in the american economy and how it relates to the price you pay for the tings you want.

The idea is a simple one my friends, it is called supply and demand.  The price of every single thing you buy is decided by a number of factors, but the biggest one of all is the fair market value, which in turn is regulated by 2 things:  The supply of the item readily available on the market, and the DEMAND for the item by the consuming public.  When the market has an excess of items available and a low demand for them by the consumers, you will see prices drop for said items.  When the demand rises and the supply starts to drop, the value of the items begins to rise, and in turn the price rises.  Once production catches up with the demand, the prices go back down.  This concept  is as old as dirt, ever since man kind began bartering and trading, and it is this concept that controls the market price for  billions of items world wide;  Including and not limited to guns and ammunition.

Ever since this scare started, I have profited a significant amount from the buying and selling of ammunition, as well as the trading of guns.  I have bought at bargain prices and sold for great profits, and not only will I not apologize for that, I will go further to say f*ck you if you have a problem with it.  This is america, this is a free market, and it is up to the individual to jump right in to it and make a dollar wherever they can.  If you do not like the idea of paying the prices that are being asked, then here's an idea.. DO NOT PAY THEM!  Wait for the market prices to go back down, or if you claim you can find the same items at a store or online cheaper...here's another idea, GO THERE AND BUY THEM! Why not just do that instead of getting on here and pissing and moaning to people and on this website about prices?  If you turn on the television and you do not like what is playing, do you write the producers sobbing about it, or do you change the f***ing channel?  It is time for everyone to put on their big boy pants and big girl panties and understand the fluctuation of the markets, and act accordingly.  This is just how the world works, and if you are not smart enough to understand that, then you likely have no business handling a firearm in the first place.

There are a lot of ways to get around the market prices in private sales.  Just OFFER what you are willing to pay to the seller.  The worst they can say is no, but you would be amazed at how many people are willing to settle to make the sale.  That is how I get my good prices, and it works.  Offer something up for a partial trade.  The fact is you may not be able to get the price you want, so offer something you can part with as a trade.  If you and the seller cannot come to an agreement, just walk away.  How hard is that?
Lets just all be adults here people.  Grow up, get with the program, and lets ride this market wave the best we can until it comes crashing back down and everyone can be happy again."
